@NODE "Shareware" "Shareware"

This software is shareware, which means that you can do just about
anything you like with it as long as you don't change the name
of the author. 

And please notify @{"me" link "author"} about any changes
(Hopefully improvements) that you've made to this software so
that I can update the archieve.

See @{" Author " link "Author"} for my address.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Introduction" "Introduction"

I've always wanted a MP3 player for the Amiga that's good-
looking and tiny. In fact I wanted it so tiny that I would
be able to use it on my Workbench screen without taking up
half the desktop.

This is the reason why I started looking for an MP3-player
that could do this. I found several of them, but noone could
really satisfy my hunger;

AmigaAMP by Thomas Wenzel - Tiny, but ugly looking. This was
improved with V2.0 of the program, where I could make my own
skins for the program, but it still lacked some important
features like a decent VU-meter.

Tmg (don't know the author) - Big and with an ugly GUI.

Songplayer by Stéphane Tavenard - Lot's of features, good
looking, but to bulky.

I found that the easiest way to make an MP3 player that 
suited my need's was to either make a GUI of my own or to
modify one of the existing one's. I chose the latter. And 
'Songplayer' seemed like a good starting point because of
it's use of MUI.

And this is the result. Check out the pictures in the 
'Example pictures' for an idea of what your songplayer could
look like.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Requirements" "Requirements"

REQUIREMENTS

    - An Amiga.

    - The fastest CPU you can find (Well, not really. But, hey!
      wouldn't it be fun to have a faster amiga? :))

    - MUI v3.1 or better
	 
    - Songplayer v1.2 or better by Stéphane Tavenard (Aminet) 
	 
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Installation" "Installation"

INSTALLATION

* Make sure that 'Songplayer' (See @{" requirements " link "Requirements"})
  is installed correctly onto your HD. 

* Then you simply copy the contents of the 'songplayer'-directory 
  in the TinySongplayer-archieve to your songplayer-dir.

* copy the fonts-dir to fonts:

* copy the envarc-dir to your envarc:.

* Set your screenmode to at least 32-colours

And Voila! Congratulation's with a new and improved Songplayer! 

@ENDNODE



@NODE "History" "History"

HISTORY

History? What history? This is my first official release
of this new and improved songplayer-GUI...

@ENDNODE



@NODE "Problems" "Problems"

PROBLEMS

The only problem you should encounter is that the colour of your
new GUI might be slightly different than the one shown in the
example pictures, but this can easily be altered with the prefs-
program in Songplayer


@ENDNODE


